videos.description: Ty Cummings kickoff for 65-yards , Malik Williams return for 14-yards to the Lvile 14 Malik Williams fumbled, recovered by Houst
videos.headline: Louisville fumbles away the opening kickoff

videos.description: After Louisville fumbles the opening kickoff, Houston's Greg Ward Jr. tosses a short pass to Duke Catalon, who scores a 13-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Houston strikes 11 seconds into the game

videos.description: For the second time in the first quarter, Houston forces a fumble and retrieves the ball in Louisville territory. This time, Cardinals running back Brandon Radcliff gets the ball stripped and it is eventually recovered by the Cougars' Cameron Malveaux.
videos.headline: Houston recovers another Louisville fumble

videos.description: On fourth-and-13, Houston punter Dane Roy passes to Byron Simpson for a 15-yard gain, which would lead to another Cougars' touchdown.
videos.headline: Houston fools Louisville on fake punt

videos.description: Houston's Greg Ward Jr. evades pressure and his pass gets deflected by a Louisville defender right into the hands of Duke Catalon in the end zone for a 13-yard touchdown in the second quarter.
videos.headline: Houston adds to lead over No. 5 Louisville on deflected pass

videos.description: Houston running back Duke Catalon stretches over the goal line to score a 2-yard touchdown, his third of the first half, extending the Cougars' lead to 24-0 over the No. 5 Cardinals.
videos.headline: Catalon's third TD of half extends Houston's lead over No. 5 Louisville

videos.description: Greg Ward Jr. tosses a lateral to wide receiver Linell Bonner, who then throws deep downfield to a wide-open Chance Allen to extend Houston's lead over No.5 Louisville to 31-0.
videos.headline: Trick play continues Houston's rout of No. 5 Louisville

videos.description: Louisville head coach Bobby Petrino talks about his teams need to sustain blocks and avoid penalties
videos.headline: Louisville head coach Bobby Petrino talks about his teams need to sustain blocks and avoid penalties

videos.description: Houston head coach Tom Herman talks about his teams need to continue to contain Louisville's offense
videos.headline: Houston head coach Tom Herman talks about his teams need to continue to contain Louisville's offense

videos.description: On fourth-and-3, Lamar Jackson lobs a pass to Cole Hikutini to score a 12-yard touchdown, getting No. 5 Louisville on the board but trailing Houston 31-7.
videos.headline: No. 5 Louisville gets on the board with fourth-down TD pass

videos.description: With No. 5 Louisville in the red zone, Lamar Jackson scrambles outside the pocket and fumbles the ball. It gets recovered by Houston for the third fumble recovery for the Cougars in the game.
videos.headline: Jackson fumbles ball as No. 5 Louisville loses momentum

videos.description: Duke Catalon run for a loss of 1 yard to the Lvile 28
videos.headline: No. 5 Louisville gets crucial 4th down stop

videos.description: Lamar Jackson sacked by Steven Taylor for a loss of 5 yards to the Lvile 28
videos.headline: Steven Taylor takes down Lamar Jackson for Houston's 10th sack of the game

videos.description: With No. 5 Louisville down late in the fourth quarter, Lamar Jackson gets pressured and throws the ball from the end zone. It gets ruled a safety, extending Houston's lead to 36-10.
videos.headline: Houston's D continues to pressure Jackson, results in a safety

videos.description: Houston head coach Tom Herman talks about the defensive aggresiveness that lead his team to a 36-10 win over No. 5 Louisville
videos.headline: Houston head coach Tom Herman talks about the defensive aggresiveness that lead his team to a 36-10 win over No. 5 Louisville

videos.description: Jesse Palmer joins SVP to break down what effect Louisville's loss will have on the College Football Playoff picture.
videos.headline: Louisville's loss adds to CFP chaos

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Analysis (Louisville's loss adds to CFP chaos) 2016/11/17 SVP SC

videos.description: Houston coach Tom Herman joins SVP to talk about what beating No. 5 Louisville means for the Cougars' football program.
videos.headline: Herman says win proves Houston can play with anyone

tracking.trackingName: COM_NCF Interview (Herman says win proves Houston can play with anyone) 2016/11/17 SVP SC

videos.description: Louisville v Houston post game breakdown on Houston's dominant defensive performance in their 36-10 victory over No. 5 Louisville
videos.headline: Louisville v Houston post game breakdown on Houston's dominant defensive performance in their 36-10 victory over No. 5 Louisville

videos.description: Bobby Petrino says Louisville blew a golden opportunity losing to Houston.
videos.headline: Petrino: 'We blew it'
